					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I was just talking this over with kevtris, and he came up with what I think is a great solution - have the initial bootloader use both D0 and D1.  The only thing AFAIK that uses D1 is Famicom expansion controllers (where it is the 'normal' data-in).  So between D0 and D1, the bootloader would then be compatible with controller port serial adapters, NES expansion port serial adapters, and Famicom expansion port serial adapters (Famicom has hard-wired controllers), all at the same time.  Can't beat that for flexibility and compatibility.</div>

