						<div class="postbody">Oh also, I believe the Famicom expansion D1 will be on $4016 (I think so, but I'm not sure).  So it's a different bit and a different register.  Still, not too bad though.
<br />
<br />As for noise on the lines, kevtris said some NES games (such as Spelunker) already check this bit.  So it must be stable, but I suppose the NES version could be ignoring it afterwards (not sure at the moment, but I doubt that it's been changed - this is probably common on famicom games).</div>

